{"type": "root", "attrs": {"icon": "/nodes/vop/DASH--up_transport-1.0/DASH-up_transport-icon.svg", "type": "node", "context": "vop", "internal": "up_transport", "version": "1.0", "namespace": "DASH"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Up Transport"], "extent": [43, 60]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Single-step solve of a Parallel Transport Frame operation."], "extent": [60, 127]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Overview"], "extent": [127, 142], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This is a single-step solve of something akin to ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/orientalongcurve", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/orientalongcurve.html"}, ", where one is trying to find the frame for a tangent direction from a previous frame\u2019s directions."], "extent": [142, 320]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["If dealing with a polypath curve one can actually use the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Tangent(Z Axis)"]}, " attribute from ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/orientalongcurve", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/orientalongcurve.html"}, " for both forwards. If dealing with a simulation, one can use the previous and current frame velocities as forwards. The initial up vector is to be defined or sourced from a previous frame, which is then transported to the next frame."], "extent": [320, 676]}]}, {"level": 1, "id": "parameters", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [676, 688], "body": [{"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Transport"], "extent": [688, 705], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Next Forward"], "extent": [705, 720], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Next frame\u2019s forward/tangent/Zaxis."], "extent": [738, 779]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "next_fwd"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Previous Up"], "extent": [779, 792], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Previous frame\u2019s up/normal/Yaxis."], "extent": [809, 848]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "prev_up"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Previous Forward"], "extent": [848, 866], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Next frame\u2019s forward/tangent/Zaxis."], "extent": [884, 925]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "prev_fwd"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Average Forward"], "extent": [925, 942], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Uses an average of ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Next Forward"]}, " and ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Previous Forward"]}, " for frame calculations and output. If using tangents form ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/orientalongcurve", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/orientalongcurve.html"}, ", its best to set its ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Tangent Type"]}, " parameter to ", {"type": "em", "text": ["Next Edge"]}, ", if this is to be used."], "extent": [963, 1201]}, {"type": "fig_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "fig", "indent": 4, "text": [" ", {"scheme": "Image", "value": "/nodes/vop/DASH--up_transport-1.0/DASH-up_transport-help_average_forward.svg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "role": "item", "extent": [1201, 1270], "body": [], "container": true, "attrs": {"display": "half left"}}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "average_fwd"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Method Bias"], "extent": [1303, 1316], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["There are two methods to solve the up transport; one produces one more perpedicular to both forwards, the other, one more coplanar to both forwards and this method blends between them."], "extent": [1337, 1526]}, {"type": "fig_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "fig", "indent": 4, "text": [" ", {"scheme": "Image", "value": "/nodes/vop/DASH--up_transport-1.0/DASH-up_transport-help_method_bias.png", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "role": "item", "extent": [1526, 1591], "body": [{"type": "summary", "indent": 8, "text": ["Progression of a vertical direction, {0,1,0}, transported multiple times with different values of Method Bias."], "extent": [1619, 1745]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"display": "wide left"}}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "method_bias"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Alignment"], "extent": [1745, 1761], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The transported up vector can also be aligned to an explicit direction or an auto-banking direction, based on the curvature between the forward directions."], "extent": [1761, 1919]}, {"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Align Amount"], "extent": [1919, 1933], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["How much should be the new up vector be transformed to either align to ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Target Direction"]}, " or the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Bank Direction"]}, "."], "extent": [1948, 2072]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "align"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Align Angle Limit"], "extent": [2072, 2091], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["This avoids the alignment rotation to go above a specific angle value. This parameter\u2019s UI is in degrees, more human-friendly, but the input port connection expects values in radians, more trigonometry-friendly. Be aware of these differences."], "extent": [2112, 2360]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "align_limit"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Align Target/Bank Bias"], "extent": [2360, 2384], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["At ", {"type": "code", "text": ["0"]}, " the alignment will be totally to ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Target Direction"]}, ", while at ", {"type": "code", "text": ["1"]}, " the alignment will be totally towards the auto-banking."], "extent": [2408, 2544]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "align_dir_bias"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Target Direction"], "extent": [2544, 2562], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Direction to align the transported up vector towards, while still being perpedicular to forward."], "extent": [2582, 2684]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "target_dir"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Target As Line"], "extent": [2684, 2700], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["When the target direction would require, for example, a 135\u00ba rotation, activating this will instead only require a -45\u00ba rotation, a shorter rotation, keeping the current up more stable."], "extent": [2721, 2911]}, {"type": "fig_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "fig", "indent": 4, "text": [" ", {"scheme": "Image", "value": "/nodes/vop/DASH--up_transport-1.0/DASH-up_transport-help_target_as_line.svg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "role": "item", "extent": [2911, 2979], "body": [{"type": "summary", "indent": 8, "text": ["With Target as Line activated the shortest rotation to line direction, not vector, will be picked."], "extent": [3007, 3121]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"display": "wide left"}}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "target_line"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Bank In/Out Direction"], "extent": [3121, 3144], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["When auto-banking this determines if the alignment will be towards the inside or outside of the curve, or even the closest perpendicular direction."], "extent": [3162, 3314]}, {"type": "fig_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "fig", "indent": 4, "text": [" ", {"scheme": "Image", "value": "/nodes/vop/DASH--up_transport-1.0/DASH-up_transport-help_bank_direction.svg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "role": "item", "extent": [3314, 3382], "body": [{"type": "summary", "indent": 8, "text": ["Bank towards the inside of the curve at 0.0, towards outside at 1.0, and towards the closest perpedicular direction at 0.5 ."], "extent": [3410, 3550]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"display": "wide left"}}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "bank_dir"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Array Auto Resize"], "extent": [3550, 3576], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Common Size"], "extent": [3576, 3589], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 2, "text": ["Determines the size that all input arrays will have. ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Min"]}, " will use the smallest array\u2019s size, while ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Max"]}, " will use the greatest array\u2019s size."], "extent": [3618, 3768]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "array_autoresize_size"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Fill"], "extent": [3768, 3774], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 2, "text": ["Sized up arrays need a fill value. This determines whether the fill is the parameter\u2019s ", {"type": "em", "text": ["Default"]}, " or, if the array is not empty, its ", {"type": "em", "text": ["Last"]}, " or ", {"type": "em", "text": ["First"]}, " value."], "extent": [3803, 3963]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "array_autoresize_fill"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 3, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "extent": [3963, 3973], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Description"], "extent": [3973, 3986], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 2, "text": ["String to display info on top of the node in the network view. The pilcrow \u00b6 button enables multi-line text."], "extent": [4005, 4117]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "description"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}]}], "text": "Parameters"}, {"level": 1, "id": "outputs", "container": true, "type": "outputs_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [4117, 4126], "body": [{"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["up"]}], "extent": [4126, 4133], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Transported up vector."], "extent": [4144, 4172]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "up"}}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["fwd"]}], "extent": [4172, 4179], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Used forward vector. Affected by ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Average Forward"]}, "."], "extent": [4191, 4250]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "fwd"}}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["tform"]}], "extent": [4250, 4259], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["3\u00d73 Matrix created from ", {"type": "ui", "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["fwd"]}]}, " and ", {"type": "ui", "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["up"]}]}, "."], "extent": [4273, 4326]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "tform"}}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["case"]}], "extent": [4326, 4334], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Code value reporting the validity of the inputs or special cases of the operation."], "extent": [4347, 4434]}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["-2"]}, ": Both Forwards have zero length. Output ", {"type": "ui", "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["up"]}]}, " is just a copy of the input."], "extent": [4434, 4523]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["-1"]}, ": Previous Up vector has zero length. Output ", {"type": "ui", "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["up"]}]}, " is just a copy of the input, zero."], "extent": [4523, 4622]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": [" 0"]}, ": Up and Forwards directions are all valid. Not zero lengths."], "extent": [4622, 4694]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": [" 1"]}, ": Both Forwards are colinear, pointing in the same or in opposite directions."], "extent": [4694, 4782]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": [" 2"]}, ": Up vector is colinear to Next Forward."], "extent": [4782, 4833]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": [" 3"]}, ": Both ", {"type": "code", "text": ["1"]}, " and ", {"type": "code", "text": ["2"]}, " cases."], "extent": [4833, 4869]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": [" 4"]}, ": Previous Forward has zero length."], "extent": [4869, 4915]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": [" 5"]}, ": Next Forward has zero length."], "extent": [4915, 4958]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "case"}}], "container": true}, {"type": "load_example_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "load_example", "indent": 0, "text": [" Up Transport"], "role": "item", "extent": [4958, 4986], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Example scene for this asset."], "extent": [5037, 5071]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"examplefile": "/demos/vop/up_transport_demo.hda"}}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "text": "Outputs"}], "title": ["Up Transport"], "summary": ["Single-step solve of a Parallel Transport Frame operation."]}